07/03/2007
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal announced on Tuesday (March 6th) the short text of the indictment against three Croatian generals, Ante Gotovina, Ivan Cermak and Mladen Markac. 
The court will hear six of the 20 counts provided by prosecutors, stemming from alleged war crimes committed during the Croatian military's Operation Storm in 1995. 
The trial is expected to begin in early May. 
(Vecernji list - 07/03/07; HINA, HRT - 06/03/07)
